Description.text: Please note that all quantitations are performed on a tif image and not a JPEG. The Image positions reported in this MAGE document refer to positions on the original tif. If a JPEG is supplied with this MAGE document then the position must be divided by the down sampling factor supplied in the Feature Extraction Application Protocol.

Ratio of estimated feature covariance in RedGreen space to product of feature Standard Deviation in Red Green space. The covariance of two features measures their tendency to vary together, i.e., to co-vary. In this case, it is a cumulative quantitation of the tendency of pixels belonging to a particular feature in Red and Green spaces to co-vary.

Boolean flag indicating if a feature is a Population Outlier or not. Probes with replicate features on a microarray are examined using population statistics. A feature is a population outlier if its signal is less than a lower threshold or exceeds an upper threshold determined using the interquartile range (i.e., IQR) of the population. A 1 indicates Feature is a population outlier

Set to one if the quantitation values of a feature are considered bad enough to thrown out in the higher level analysis. Features are thrown out if both channels are saturated or if either channel is a non-uniform outlier. A feature can be failed from outside of feature extraction via setting this flag when loading the design or grid.
